title: 1.4.1 - Uncertainty in Environmental Science
section 1_4_1

  |Science always involves {Topics.*Uncertainty uncertainties}. These arise at each step of the scientific method. Climate science is not different in this regard from other areas of science. The complexity of the climate system and the large range of processes involved bring particular challenges. This report highlights the influence of model uncertainty, scenario uncertainty, and {Topics.*Climate_Variability internal variability}, among other sources uncertainty.


  

